SegmentSflowStatus.name: SegmentSflowStatus
SegmentSflowStatus.description: An indication of sFlow enable/disable/applicable status for a segment

segmentEntry.name: segmentEntry
segmentEntry.description: An entry in the segment table. Rows cannot be created or deleted.

slotIndex.name: slotIndex
slotIndex.description: The slot index, starting with 1. For older platforms like N-platforms and Lowball, all the segments are assumed to be on slot 1.

segmentSflowStatus.name: segmentSflowStatus
segmentSflowStatus.description: sFlow status of the segment. Not applicable on Lowball platforms (10/110/330). For those platforms, the value will be set to not-applicable.

sFlowDivisor.name: sFlowDivisor
sFlowDivisor.description: The sFlow divisor value of the segment. Not applicable on the Lowball platforms (10/110/330). For those platforms, the value will be set to 0.
